00:00:13.850 --> 00:00:16.129 align:middle line:84%
what they write,
or speak, or do.

00:00:16.129 --> 00:00:18.110 align:middle line:90%
That's all about to change.

00:00:18.110 --> 00:00:20.240 align:middle line:84%
Neuralink is one
of the new channels

00:00:20.240 --> 00:00:23.070 align:middle line:84%
that will allow us to interface
directly with the brain.

00:00:23.070 --> 00:00:25.520 align:middle line:84%
One of the things you can do
with a Neuralink interface

00:00:25.520 --> 00:00:27.230 align:middle line:84%
or any sort of
computer interface

00:00:27.230 --> 00:00:30.530 align:middle line:84%
is learn how to remotely operate
heavy equipment, a machine,

00:00:30.530 --> 00:00:33.030 align:middle line:84%
as if you're putting
on a robot body.

00:00:33.030 --> 00:00:36.590 align:middle line:84%
>> Are you scared about
artificial intelligence?

00:00:36.590 --> 00:00:39.960 align:middle line:84%
>> I have a very cautionary
feeling about it.

00:00:39.960 --> 00:00:43.190 align:middle line:84%
We are now at the point where
the growth of information

00:00:43.190 --> 00:00:45.620 align:middle line:84%
and knowledge is
outstripping our ability

00:00:45.620 --> 00:00:47.780 align:middle line:90%
to appreciate and understand it.

00:00:47.780 --> 00:00:50.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Should we stop
doing what we're doing?

00:00:50.300 --> 00:00:51.408 align:middle line:90%
>> You can't.

00:00:51.408 --> 00:00:52.700 align:middle line:90%
The genie is out of the bottle.

00:00:52.700 --> 00:00:53.500 align:middle line:90%
>> It is.

00:00:53.500 --> 00:00:55.730 align:middle line:84%
>> The problem,
in my estimation,

00:00:55.730 --> 00:01:00.150 align:middle line:84%
is that we don't teach people
ethics along with technology.

00:01:00.150 --> 00:01:04.538 align:middle line:90%


00:01:04.538 --> 00:01:06.330 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE NOORY: Welcome
to "Beyond Belief."

00:01:06.330 --> 00:01:09.810 align:middle line:10%
Sir Charles Shults III worked
at Martin Marietta Aerospace

00:01:09.810 --> 00:01:13.800 align:middle line:10%
for 10 years on weapons systems
and computer-based automated

00:01:13.800 --> 00:01:14.610 align:middle line:10%
test equipment.

00:01:14.610 --> 00:01:17.580 align:middle line:84%
Now, he wrote the
nuclear EMP test

00:01:17.580 --> 00:01:21.900 align:middle line:84%
software and many other notable
military aerospace projects.

00:01:21.900 --> 00:01:24.360 align:middle line:84%
He has been knighted
and is currently

00:01:24.360 --> 00:01:27.970 align:middle line:84%
working on research in robotics
and artificial intelligence.

00:01:27.970 --> 00:01:30.190 align:middle line:84%
Sir Charles, always
great to talk to you.

00:01:30.190 --> 00:01:30.760 align:middle line:84%
>>CHARLES SHULTS III:
Thank you, George.

00:01:30.760 --> 00:01:31.900 align:middle line:90%
It's a real pleasure to be here.

00:01:31.900 --> 00:01:33.705 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We finally meet
after all these years.

00:01:33.705 --> 00:01:34.980 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: It's taken 18 years.

00:01:34.980 --> 00:01:35.310 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:01:35.310 --> 00:01:37.620 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How did you get
involved in all of this?

00:01:37.620 --> 00:01:39.665 align:middle line:10%
>>SHULTS: I've always been
fascinated by science,

00:01:39.665 --> 00:01:41.040 align:middle line:10%
and I always wanted
to understand

00:01:41.040 --> 00:01:41.820 align:middle line:10%
how everything worked.

00:01:41.820 --> 00:01:44.112 align:middle line:10%
When I was a child, I figured
I'd be living and working

00:01:44.112 --> 00:01:46.320 align:middle line:10%
in space, so I'd better
learn everything I possibly

00:01:46.320 --> 00:01:48.690 align:middle line:10%
could just to make myself
capable of supporting

00:01:48.690 --> 00:01:50.220 align:middle line:10%
that sort of a lifestyle.

00:01:50.220 --> 00:01:51.540 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: You love space too.

00:01:51.540 --> 00:01:52.580 align:middle line:10%
>>SHULTS: I absolutely
love it, yes.

00:01:52.580 --> 00:01:54.247 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Were you so
excited about Mars,

00:01:54.247 --> 00:01:56.425 align:middle line:10%
and those anomalies you
found, and stuff like that?

00:01:56.425 --> 00:01:57.300 align:middle line:10%
>>SHULTS: Absolutely.

00:01:57.300 --> 00:02:00.220 align:middle line:84%
And it's something I feel
people should know about.

00:02:00.220 --> 00:02:01.810 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You have
dealt with something

00:02:01.810 --> 00:02:06.730 align:middle line:84%
that is coming across this
planet in record numbers,

00:02:06.730 --> 00:02:09.009 align:middle line:84%
and that is the
Neuralink system.

00:02:09.009 --> 00:02:10.840 align:middle line:90%
I mean how do you explain that?

00:02:10.840 --> 00:02:13.750 align:middle line:84%
Hardly a night doesn't go
by on my radio show where

00:02:13.750 --> 00:02:15.610 align:middle line:84%
somebody calls in
and says, George,

00:02:15.610 --> 00:02:18.340 align:middle line:90%
there are 25 UFOs up there.

00:02:18.340 --> 00:02:20.980 align:middle line:84%
It's the Neuralink
satellite system.

00:02:20.980 --> 00:02:21.820 align:middle line:90%
What is it?

00:02:21.820 --> 00:02:23.350 align:middle line:84%
>>SHULTS: [LAUGHS]
Well, Neuralink

00:02:23.350 --> 00:02:25.642 align:middle line:84%
doesn't have anything to do
with satellites, of course.

00:02:25.642 --> 00:02:28.445 align:middle line:84%
It's actually based on
a very simple premise.

00:02:28.445 --> 00:02:30.070 align:middle line:84%
Through all of history,
the human brain

00:02:30.070 --> 00:02:32.733 align:middle line:84%
has been an isolated
item, and the only way

00:02:32.733 --> 00:02:34.150 align:middle line:84%
you know what's
in a person's mind

00:02:34.150 --> 00:02:37.090 align:middle line:84%
is through what they
write, or speak, or do.

00:02:37.090 --> 00:02:39.070 align:middle line:90%
That's all about to change.

00:02:39.070 --> 00:02:41.260 align:middle line:84%
Neuralink is one
of the new channels

00:02:41.260 --> 00:02:44.150 align:middle line:84%
that will allow us to interface
directly with the brain.

00:02:44.150 --> 00:02:46.360 align:middle line:84%
And there are two of
those types of channels

00:02:46.360 --> 00:02:47.600 align:middle line:90%
that exist right now.

00:02:47.600 --> 00:02:49.690 align:middle line:90%
One of them is functional MRI.

00:02:49.690 --> 00:02:54.220 align:middle line:84%
We have people who are comatose
and unresponsive and unable

00:02:54.220 --> 00:02:55.450 align:middle line:90%
to communicate.

00:02:55.450 --> 00:02:57.970 align:middle line:84%
Well, we have a means of seeing
what's in their mind now.

00:02:57.970 --> 00:02:59.980 align:middle line:84%
We literally can get a
picture of what they're

00:02:59.980 --> 00:03:01.400 align:middle line:90%
imagining in their heads.

00:03:01.400 --> 00:03:03.220 align:middle line:84%
And so they've found
anywhere from one out

00:03:03.220 --> 00:03:04.970 align:middle line:84%
of three to one out
of six of these people

00:03:04.970 --> 00:03:07.880 align:middle line:84%
are fully aware but
unable to say anything.

00:03:07.880 --> 00:03:09.310 align:middle line:84%
And so they'll
say, OK, I'm going

00:03:09.310 --> 00:03:11.320 align:middle line:84%
to ask you some questions,
yes-or-no questions.

00:03:11.320 --> 00:03:14.050 align:middle line:84%
And if the answer is yes,
think of a green square.

00:03:14.050 --> 00:03:16.510 align:middle line:84%
And if the answer is no,
think of a red triangle.

00:03:16.510 --> 00:03:17.890 align:middle line:90%
And then they talk to them.

00:03:17.890 --> 00:03:19.480 align:middle line:84%
And looking at the
monitor, they can

00:03:19.480 --> 00:03:22.418 align:middle line:84%
see what that person is
visualizing in the head,

00:03:22.418 --> 00:03:24.460 align:middle line:84%
and they've established
communications with them.

00:03:24.460 --> 00:03:25.610 align:middle line:90%
Well, now this is amazing.

00:03:25.610 --> 00:03:29.020 align:middle line:84%
We can see locked-in people
actually are many times aware.

00:03:29.020 --> 00:03:32.710 align:middle line:84%
Well, now Neuralink gives
us a direct channel.

00:03:32.710 --> 00:03:35.050 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if you're aware
of the experiments that

00:03:35.050 --> 00:03:38.560 align:middle line:84%
were done by Elon Musk's group
to teach a monkey to play

00:03:38.560 --> 00:03:39.760 align:middle line:90%
a video game such as pong.

00:03:39.760 --> 00:03:40.510 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yes, amazing.

00:03:40.510 --> 00:03:41.890 align:middle line:84%
>>SHULTS: And so
they plant a chip

00:03:41.890 --> 00:03:43.890 align:middle line:84%
about the size of a postage
stamp with thousands

00:03:43.890 --> 00:03:46.870 align:middle line:84%
of tiny electrodes, like
needles, into the tissue

00:03:46.870 --> 00:03:49.600 align:middle line:84%
of the brain in an area where
there's a map of your body

00:03:49.600 --> 00:03:51.070 align:middle line:90%
called the homunculus.

00:03:51.070 --> 00:03:53.230 align:middle line:84%
And when you think
of moving, there's

00:03:53.230 --> 00:03:55.910 align:middle line:84%
a certain firing
pattern of neurons.

00:03:55.910 --> 00:03:58.870 align:middle line:84%
So they collect that firing
pattern through Bluetooth

00:03:58.870 --> 00:04:01.000 align:middle line:90%
to a program that analyzes it.

00:04:01.000 --> 00:04:04.360 align:middle line:84%
And the program figures
out predictably where

00:04:04.360 --> 00:04:05.630 align:middle line:90%
you're going to move.

00:04:05.630 --> 00:04:07.690 align:middle line:84%
And so the monkey
used a joystick.

00:04:07.690 --> 00:04:11.530 align:middle line:84%
And the program figured out what
his moves were going to be--

00:04:11.530 --> 00:04:12.865 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Before he did it.

00:04:12.865 --> 00:04:13.480 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: --before he did it.

00:04:13.480 --> 00:04:15.040 align:middle line:84%
Then they disconnect
the joystick.

00:04:15.040 --> 00:04:16.990 align:middle line:84%
And the monkey's
playing the game,

00:04:16.990 --> 00:04:20.350 align:middle line:84%
but the actual link is through
the Neuralink to the game.

00:04:20.350 --> 00:04:22.330 align:middle line:90%
Then they remove the joystick.

00:04:22.330 --> 00:04:24.520 align:middle line:84%
And the monkey sees
the game and thinks

00:04:24.520 --> 00:04:26.680 align:middle line:84%
about the movements
he would make,

00:04:26.680 --> 00:04:29.530 align:middle line:84%
and the computer sends
those codes to the program

00:04:29.530 --> 00:04:31.120 align:middle line:90%
and plays the game.

00:04:31.120 --> 00:04:33.590 align:middle line:90%
Now, why is this important?

00:04:33.590 --> 00:04:36.850 align:middle line:84%
There are many people who are
paralyzed, whether paraplegic,

00:04:36.850 --> 00:04:38.680 align:middle line:90%
or quadriplegic, or worse.

00:04:38.680 --> 00:04:41.840 align:middle line:84%
And they don't have a
means of communicating.

00:04:41.840 --> 00:04:44.170 align:middle line:84%
So this gives them the
ability to interface

00:04:44.170 --> 00:04:48.140 align:middle line:84%
an artificial nerve system
or actually augment their own

00:04:48.140 --> 00:04:50.020 align:middle line:90%
so they can regain control.

00:04:50.020 --> 00:04:52.660 align:middle line:84%
They could even add
limbs that are missing,

00:04:52.660 --> 00:04:55.545 align:middle line:84%
such as prosthetics, and control
them directly by thinking.

00:04:55.545 --> 00:04:56.920 align:middle line:84%
So this is one of
the many things

00:04:56.920 --> 00:04:58.188 align:middle line:90%
you could do with Neuralink.

00:04:58.188 --> 00:05:00.730 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There would be chips
in your head, literally, right?

00:05:00.730 --> 00:05:01.605 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: Absolutely.

00:05:01.605 --> 00:05:04.233 align:middle line:84%
And in most cases, they're about
the size of a postage stamp.

00:05:04.233 --> 00:05:06.400 align:middle line:84%
There's a company called
Synchron that's making them

00:05:06.400 --> 00:05:08.020 align:middle line:90%
about an inch and a half long.

00:05:08.020 --> 00:05:10.870 align:middle line:84%
And they're one of the major
competitors with Elon Musk's

00:05:10.870 --> 00:05:12.202 align:middle line:90%
company, Neuralink.

00:05:12.202 --> 00:05:13.660 align:middle line:84%
One of the things
they discovered--

00:05:13.660 --> 00:05:15.220 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: He's the one
putting up the satellites.

00:05:15.220 --> 00:05:15.880 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: Well, yes.

00:05:15.880 --> 00:05:18.422 align:middle line:84%
He's putting up satellites, but
they're for Starlink internet

00:05:18.422 --> 00:05:19.330 align:middle line:90%
communication.

00:05:19.330 --> 00:05:21.980 align:middle line:84%
And actually, it
works pretty well.

00:05:21.980 --> 00:05:23.710 align:middle line:84%
It depends on the
area you're in.

00:05:23.710 --> 00:05:25.330 align:middle line:84%
And it's so popular,
I think they're

00:05:25.330 --> 00:05:26.110 align:middle line:90%
running out of channels.

00:05:26.110 --> 00:05:26.980 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:05:26.980 --> 00:05:28.060 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:05:28.060 --> 00:05:29.860 align:middle line:84%
>>SHULTS: Well, I
would get it myself,

00:05:29.860 --> 00:05:32.320 align:middle line:84%
but it's not available in
the area where I'm moving.

00:05:32.320 --> 00:05:35.337 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Would you get a chip
in your brain if you needed it?

00:05:35.337 --> 00:05:37.420 align:middle line:84%
>>SHULTS: I don't think
that I would at this time.

00:05:37.420 --> 00:05:40.870 align:middle line:84%
I feel that the-- you
never buy the earliest

00:05:40.870 --> 00:05:42.307 align:middle line:90%
version of a technology.

00:05:42.307 --> 00:05:44.140 align:middle line:84%
And that's one of the
reasons I put forward.

00:05:44.140 --> 00:05:45.640 align:middle line:84%
I would wait until it
was more developed.

00:05:45.640 --> 00:05:46.598 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: With anything?

00:05:46.598 --> 00:05:48.370 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: With anything, sure.

00:05:48.370 --> 00:05:50.020 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What are
the benefits of doing

00:05:50.020 --> 00:05:51.370 align:middle line:90%
this long-range, though?

00:05:51.370 --> 00:05:52.170 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: OK.

00:05:52.170 --> 00:05:54.700 align:middle line:84%
So imagine you have to
work in an extremely

00:05:54.700 --> 00:05:55.645 align:middle line:90%
dangerous environment.

00:05:55.645 --> 00:05:57.520 align:middle line:84%
You'd rather have a
robot in that environment

00:05:57.520 --> 00:05:59.410 align:middle line:84%
than a human being
that could die.

00:05:59.410 --> 00:06:02.650 align:middle line:84%
And so one of the things you can
do with a Neuralink interface

00:06:02.650 --> 00:06:04.360 align:middle line:84%
or any sort of
computer interface

00:06:04.360 --> 00:06:07.660 align:middle line:84%
is learn how to remotely operate
heavy equipment, a machine,

00:06:07.660 --> 00:06:10.210 align:middle line:84%
as if you're putting
on a robot body.

00:06:10.210 --> 00:06:11.610 align:middle line:84%
You can work in
areas where there

00:06:11.610 --> 00:06:13.480 align:middle line:84%
are pressures, or
temperatures, or radiation

00:06:13.480 --> 00:06:17.650 align:middle line:84%
that would kill you instantly
by using a proxy, an avatar,

00:06:17.650 --> 00:06:18.910 align:middle line:90%
if you will.

00:06:18.910 --> 00:06:20.230 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Interesting take.

00:06:20.230 --> 00:06:23.590 align:middle line:84%
Science is moving way too
fast sometimes, Sir Charles.

00:06:23.590 --> 00:06:25.240 align:middle line:84%
>>SHULTS: Well, it
would seem, in times

00:06:25.240 --> 00:06:27.880 align:middle line:84%
past when our technology
wasn't as advanced,

00:06:27.880 --> 00:06:30.520 align:middle line:84%
we had time to see the
ramifications of things

00:06:30.520 --> 00:06:31.450 align:middle line:90%
that we were doing.

00:06:31.450 --> 00:06:33.310 align:middle line:84%
Today, that's not
necessarily the case.

00:06:33.310 --> 00:06:35.860 align:middle line:84%
Within a month, or two,
or three, or a year,

00:06:35.860 --> 00:06:37.630 align:middle line:84%
they want to go
to the next stage

00:06:37.630 --> 00:06:41.458 align:middle line:84%
without fully analyzing what
the repercussions might be.

00:06:41.458 --> 00:06:43.000 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is there
a downside to this?

00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:44.440 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: Well, there can be.

00:06:44.440 --> 00:06:47.440 align:middle line:84%
The same sort of technology
that can plug into your brain

00:06:47.440 --> 00:06:52.180 align:middle line:84%
could also be used to write
memories, or erase memories,

00:06:52.180 --> 00:06:53.890 align:middle line:90%
or alter your personality.

00:06:53.890 --> 00:06:55.570 align:middle line:84%
And I understand
from, let's say,

00:06:55.570 --> 00:06:58.960 align:middle line:84%
a psychotherapy standpoint,
this might be helpful.

00:06:58.960 --> 00:07:01.532 align:middle line:84%
But you don't want it to be
something against a person's

00:07:01.532 --> 00:07:03.490 align:middle line:84%
will, and you don't want
to do something that's

00:07:03.490 --> 00:07:06.700 align:middle line:84%
going to violate their
personal sovereignty,

00:07:06.700 --> 00:07:07.870 align:middle line:90%
in a manner of speaking.

00:07:07.870 --> 00:07:10.570 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Could they turn you
into a Manchurian Candidate?

00:07:10.570 --> 00:07:12.220 align:middle line:84%
>>SHULTS: Well, there's no
doubt that that could be done.

00:07:12.220 --> 00:07:14.387 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's been done
with psychological and drug

00:07:14.387 --> 00:07:15.550 align:middle line:90%
programming in the past.

00:07:15.550 --> 00:07:16.480 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Absolutely.

00:07:16.480 --> 00:07:18.200 align:middle line:84%
>>SHULTS: So there's
that possibility.

00:07:18.200 --> 00:07:22.492 align:middle line:84%
On the other end of this
spectrum, there are--

00:07:22.492 --> 00:07:24.700 align:middle line:84%
well, there are very good
things you can do as well--

00:07:24.700 --> 00:07:28.810 align:middle line:84%
restoring damaged memory,
possibly augmenting parts

00:07:28.810 --> 00:07:30.850 align:middle line:84%
of the brain that have
been damaged by tumors,

00:07:30.850 --> 00:07:33.490 align:middle line:90%
or illnesses, or cancer.

00:07:33.490 --> 00:07:36.170 align:middle line:84%
You can do a lot of things
with this sort of technology,

00:07:36.170 --> 00:07:39.272 align:middle line:84%
including saving
memories and experiences

00:07:39.272 --> 00:07:40.480 align:middle line:90%
that otherwise would be lost.

00:07:40.480 --> 00:07:41.938 align:middle line:84%
There's an old
African proverb that

00:07:41.938 --> 00:07:45.910 align:middle line:84%
says, "When an old man dies, a
library burns to the ground."

00:07:45.910 --> 00:07:48.250 align:middle line:84%
What if you could save
all of your experience

00:07:48.250 --> 00:07:51.430 align:middle line:84%
and the knowledge that you
would otherwise lose at death?

00:07:51.430 --> 00:07:53.260 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's like
"The Truman Show."

00:07:53.260 --> 00:07:54.790 align:middle line:84%
>>SHULTS: Well, in
some ways, it is.

00:07:54.790 --> 00:07:58.130 align:middle line:84%
And I think that a lot of people
are unaware of how deeply this

00:07:58.130 --> 00:07:58.930 align:middle line:90%
could lead.

00:07:58.930 --> 00:08:02.140 align:middle line:84%
If you can implant sensory
inputs into the mind,

00:08:02.140 --> 00:08:04.810 align:middle line:84%
you could create a false
world around somebody,

00:08:04.810 --> 00:08:08.740 align:middle line:84%
and they could live in
basically a sandbox universe

00:08:08.740 --> 00:08:11.390 align:middle line:84%
of their making or
not of their making.

00:08:11.390 --> 00:08:13.390 align:middle line:84%
So it's something to
consider that it's possible

00:08:13.390 --> 00:08:16.780 align:middle line:84%
that this could be an invasive
project that literally leads

00:08:16.780 --> 00:08:19.060 align:middle line:90%
to living in a dream world.

00:08:19.060 --> 00:08:22.060 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are they doing
this to us now, Sir Charles?

00:08:22.060 --> 00:08:23.380 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: I would doubt that.

00:08:23.380 --> 00:08:25.270 align:middle line:84%
There are certain
things that would seem

00:08:25.270 --> 00:08:27.620 align:middle line:90%
to be consistent in reality.

00:08:27.620 --> 00:08:30.500 align:middle line:84%
And if you were making
a false reality,

00:08:30.500 --> 00:08:32.419 align:middle line:84%
it would be too easy
to slip up somewhere.

00:08:32.419 --> 00:08:34.100 align:middle line:84%
I know a lot of people
might point to things like,

00:08:34.100 --> 00:08:36.070 align:middle line:84%
what they feel are
glitches in the matrix,

00:08:36.070 --> 00:08:38.140 align:middle line:90%
as you've heard of these events.

00:08:38.140 --> 00:08:40.850 align:middle line:84%
Three fellows with the same
shirt on a bus in a row.

00:08:40.850 --> 00:08:42.070 align:middle line:90%
How did that happen?

00:08:42.070 --> 00:08:44.950 align:middle line:84%
But I don't think
that we ourselves

00:08:44.950 --> 00:08:48.280 align:middle line:84%
are in a reality of
mankind's making.

00:08:48.280 --> 00:08:50.638 align:middle line:84%
Some would argue that our
whole world is a simulation,

00:08:50.638 --> 00:08:52.180 align:middle line:84%
and that's hard to
prove or disprove,

00:08:52.180 --> 00:08:53.440 align:middle line:90%
but it's a possibility.

00:08:53.440 --> 00:08:54.850 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Artificial
intelligence,

00:08:54.850 --> 00:08:57.002 align:middle line:90%
is it going too far, too fast?

00:08:57.002 --> 00:08:58.960 align:middle line:84%
>>SHULTS: I think that
one of the things people

00:08:58.960 --> 00:09:02.140 align:middle line:84%
fail to recognize is
about 90% of the funding

00:09:02.140 --> 00:09:04.420 align:middle line:84%
for the development of
artificial intelligence

00:09:04.420 --> 00:09:09.040 align:middle line:84%
comes from military
or financial projects,

00:09:09.040 --> 00:09:11.990 align:middle line:90%
and that isn't a good sign.

00:09:11.990 --> 00:09:15.340 align:middle line:84%
We often talk about the lone
inventor or the military team

00:09:15.340 --> 00:09:16.900 align:middle line:90%
programming an AI.

00:09:16.900 --> 00:09:19.090 align:middle line:84%
And you have to wonder if
such a thing they create

00:09:19.090 --> 00:09:21.450 align:middle line:84%
would actually be
sane by our standards,

00:09:21.450 --> 00:09:22.450 align:middle line:90%
and that's a real worry.

00:09:22.450 --> 00:09:23.283 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Good point.

00:09:23.283 --> 00:09:24.527 align:middle line:90%
Tell us about singularity.

00:09:24.527 --> 00:09:25.360 align:middle line:90%
What does that mean?

00:09:25.360 --> 00:09:26.710 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: Ah, the singularity.

00:09:26.710 --> 00:09:28.970 align:middle line:84%
If we look at the growth
of human knowledge,

00:09:28.970 --> 00:09:30.400 align:middle line:90%
we know that it isn't linear.

00:09:30.400 --> 00:09:33.850 align:middle line:84%
If we take the number of
facts we had at year one

00:09:33.850 --> 00:09:35.410 align:middle line:84%
and compare it to
the number of facts

00:09:35.410 --> 00:09:37.840 align:middle line:84%
we had at year 1,000
in the Middle Ages,

00:09:37.840 --> 00:09:41.590 align:middle line:84%
we can see that the
amount of knowledge about

00:09:41.590 --> 00:09:43.120 align:middle line:90%
doubled in humanity.

00:09:43.120 --> 00:09:45.430 align:middle line:84%
In another 500 years,
it doubled again.

00:09:45.430 --> 00:09:48.550 align:middle line:84%
In another quarter of a
millennium, it doubled again.

00:09:48.550 --> 00:09:51.910 align:middle line:84%
We are now at the point where
the growth of information

00:09:51.910 --> 00:09:54.340 align:middle line:84%
and knowledge is
outstripping our ability

00:09:54.340 --> 00:09:56.570 align:middle line:90%
to appreciate and understand it.

00:09:56.570 --> 00:09:58.870 align:middle line:84%
And the singularity
occurs when it

00:09:58.870 --> 00:10:01.180 align:middle line:84%
is no longer possible
to predict what

00:10:01.180 --> 00:10:03.100 align:middle line:90%
happens next on a daily basis.

00:10:03.100 --> 00:10:04.990 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Let's look
at Gaia's "Deep Space"

00:10:04.990 --> 00:10:07.337 align:middle line:84%
William Henry talking
about singularity.

00:10:07.337 --> 00:10:08.170 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: Certainly.

00:10:08.170 --> 00:10:08.970 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:10:08.970 --> 00:10:11.390 align:middle line:10%
- The singularity brings
with it the good, the bad,

00:10:11.390 --> 00:10:12.340 align:middle line:10%
and the ugly.

00:10:12.340 --> 00:10:15.580 align:middle line:10%
It can bring dramatic
changes and problem

00:10:15.580 --> 00:10:19.130 align:middle line:10%
solving for humanity in terms of
economics, physics, chemistry,

00:10:19.130 --> 00:10:19.930 align:middle line:10%
medicine.

00:10:19.930 --> 00:10:23.740 align:middle line:84%
We're talking about miraculous
new discoveries and solutions

00:10:23.740 --> 00:10:25.570 align:middle line:90%
to very human problems.

00:10:25.570 --> 00:10:28.720 align:middle line:84%
The bad is that it's
going to cost us millions

00:10:28.720 --> 00:10:30.250 align:middle line:90%
upon millions of jobs.

00:10:30.250 --> 00:10:32.770 align:middle line:10%
As much as 90% of
the human population

00:10:32.770 --> 00:10:35.980 align:middle line:10%
will be unemployed when the
singularity takes place.

00:10:35.980 --> 00:10:37.510 align:middle line:90%
That leads to the ugly.

00:10:37.510 --> 00:10:41.320 align:middle line:84%
The potential for anarchy
is absolutely astounding,

00:10:41.320 --> 00:10:44.170 align:middle line:84%
and nobody seems to be
talking about that potential

00:10:44.170 --> 00:10:47.380 align:middle line:84%
of unleashing the power of
artificial intelligence.

00:10:47.380 --> 00:10:49.720 align:middle line:84%
Take a look around your
life, your daily life.

00:10:49.720 --> 00:10:51.187 align:middle line:90%
You go into a coffee shop.

00:10:51.187 --> 00:10:52.270 align:middle line:90%
You go to the dry cleaner.

00:10:52.270 --> 00:10:53.260 align:middle line:90%
You see a policeman.

00:10:53.260 --> 00:10:54.850 align:middle line:90%
You see a taxi driver.

00:10:54.850 --> 00:10:57.550 align:middle line:84%
Any and all of
those jobs will be

00:10:57.550 --> 00:10:59.920 align:middle line:84%
eliminated from a
human perspective

00:10:59.920 --> 00:11:02.890 align:middle line:84%
and replaced by artificially
intelligent robots

00:11:02.890 --> 00:11:04.960 align:middle line:90%
within 10 years.

00:11:04.960 --> 00:11:09.070 align:middle line:84%
When we're talking about the
singularity eliminating jobs,

00:11:09.070 --> 00:11:11.590 align:middle line:84%
we're talking about
almost any job that

00:11:11.590 --> 00:11:13.690 align:middle line:90%
involves any kind of routine.

00:11:13.690 --> 00:11:18.970 align:middle line:84%
Doctors, lawyers-- eliminated,
replaced by AI robots.

00:11:18.970 --> 00:11:22.200 align:middle line:10%
Menial jobs, however-- street
sweepers and construction

00:11:22.200 --> 00:11:23.000 align:middle line:10%
workers--

00:11:23.000 --> 00:11:25.940 align:middle line:10%
this is the type of job that
is very difficult for machines

00:11:25.940 --> 00:11:26.740 align:middle line:10%
to do.

00:11:26.740 --> 00:11:29.080 align:middle line:10%
Anything that we can
do with our human hands

00:11:29.080 --> 00:11:30.940 align:middle line:10%
and involves
movement in our feet

00:11:30.940 --> 00:11:33.280 align:middle line:10%
are jobs that will
ultimately be secure.

00:11:33.280 --> 00:11:35.200 align:middle line:84%
Thinking jobs,
however, are going

00:11:35.200 --> 00:11:37.330 align:middle line:84%
to be eliminated
on a human basis

00:11:37.330 --> 00:11:39.160 align:middle line:84%
and will be replaced
by machines.

00:11:39.160 --> 00:11:41.920 align:middle line:84%
One of the advantages of
achieving the singularity

00:11:41.920 --> 00:11:44.680 align:middle line:84%
is that it unites human
intelligence with machine

00:11:44.680 --> 00:11:48.280 align:middle line:84%
intelligence to solve
human problems, problems

00:11:48.280 --> 00:11:50.950 align:middle line:84%
with the environment,
problems with biology,

00:11:50.950 --> 00:11:52.210 align:middle line:90%
problems in medicine.

00:11:52.210 --> 00:11:54.010 align:middle line:10%
If we can solve
these problems, we're

00:11:54.010 --> 00:11:57.100 align:middle line:10%
talking about miraculous
cures for diseases.

00:11:57.100 --> 00:11:59.020 align:middle line:10%
We're talking about
a new way of living.

00:11:59.020 --> 00:12:04.760 align:middle line:10%
But the cost is unparalleled
and beyond our comprehension.

00:12:04.760 --> 00:12:08.120 align:middle line:84%
Artificial intelligence can
have a revolutionary impact

00:12:08.120 --> 00:12:11.660 align:middle line:84%
on our politics, on
medicine, on our environment,

00:12:11.660 --> 00:12:14.720 align:middle line:84%
on biology because
of its ability

00:12:14.720 --> 00:12:17.600 align:middle line:84%
to access massive
amounts of data

00:12:17.600 --> 00:12:21.367 align:middle line:84%
in perceived patterns that
would take perhaps a human years

00:12:21.367 --> 00:12:22.325 align:middle line:90%
to be able to perceive.

00:12:22.325 --> 00:12:22.700 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:12:22.700 --> 00:12:25.107 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So it has some
pluses and minuses, obviously.

00:12:25.107 --> 00:12:25.940 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: Certainly.

00:12:25.940 --> 00:12:28.790 align:middle line:84%
Well, one of the things
here is, as was pointed out,

00:12:28.790 --> 00:12:31.730 align:middle line:84%
many of the intellectual
jobs can be automated.

00:12:31.730 --> 00:12:34.850 align:middle line:84%
Once you have an algorithm
for doing things properly,

00:12:34.850 --> 00:12:36.900 align:middle line:84%
that generally
becomes a solution.

00:12:36.900 --> 00:12:38.667 align:middle line:84%
But when we talk about
loss of employment,

00:12:38.667 --> 00:12:40.250 align:middle line:84%
there are a lot of
things to consider.

00:12:40.250 --> 00:12:43.730 align:middle line:84%
In the year 1200, how
many people were employed?

00:12:43.730 --> 00:12:44.780 align:middle line:90%
Everybody was.

00:12:44.780 --> 00:12:47.253 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they worked at the
business of staying alive.

00:12:47.253 --> 00:12:48.170 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's right.

00:12:48.170 --> 00:12:50.490 align:middle line:84%
>>SHULTS: When we look at
how we lived in the 1950s,

00:12:50.490 --> 00:12:53.900 align:middle line:84%
'60s, and '70s, there was a
survey done that said, in order

00:12:53.900 --> 00:12:57.740 align:middle line:84%
to provide the level of service
that we experience in our life

00:12:57.740 --> 00:13:01.220 align:middle line:84%
due to simple devices like
refrigeration and vehicles,

00:13:01.220 --> 00:13:05.780 align:middle line:84%
it would take about 86
slaves' equivalent of effort

00:13:05.780 --> 00:13:09.000 align:middle line:84%
to give us that level of
living, that standard of living.

00:13:09.000 --> 00:13:10.580 align:middle line:84%
Now we're in a
position where it's

00:13:10.580 --> 00:13:12.590 align:middle line:84%
hard to gauge that because
a lot of what we do

00:13:12.590 --> 00:13:14.430 align:middle line:90%
is based on information.

00:13:14.430 --> 00:13:17.510 align:middle line:84%
So I think the big
flaw in this reasoning

00:13:17.510 --> 00:13:20.480 align:middle line:84%
is that you must be
gainfully employed

00:13:20.480 --> 00:13:23.720 align:middle line:84%
in the system that runs
the economy in order to be

00:13:23.720 --> 00:13:26.130 align:middle line:90%
a positive asset to humanity.

00:13:26.130 --> 00:13:28.010 align:middle line:84%
I think that a lot of
people could live off

00:13:28.010 --> 00:13:30.380 align:middle line:84%
grid and quite
successfully on their own

00:13:30.380 --> 00:13:33.120 align:middle line:84%
without any bad effects
on the rest of us.

00:13:33.120 --> 00:13:35.360 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Sir Charles, are
we going to have robocops

00:13:35.360 --> 00:13:36.842 align:middle line:90%
like William Henry predicted?

00:13:36.842 --> 00:13:38.300 align:middle line:84%
>>SHULTS: There's
no doubt of that.

00:13:38.300 --> 00:13:42.110 align:middle line:84%
You may remember the big
dog by Boston Dynamics,

00:13:42.110 --> 00:13:44.570 align:middle line:84%
the four-legged runaround
pack carrier robot.

00:13:44.570 --> 00:13:46.580 align:middle line:90%
They have smaller versions now.

00:13:46.580 --> 00:13:49.273 align:middle line:84%
And they have recently
appeared armed.

00:13:49.273 --> 00:13:50.690 align:middle line:84%
And it's been said
that they'll be

00:13:50.690 --> 00:13:53.437 align:middle line:84%
used on front lines and
patrolling military borders

00:13:53.437 --> 00:13:54.395 align:middle line:90%
and this sort of thing.

00:13:54.395 --> 00:13:54.990 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Wow.

00:13:54.990 --> 00:13:56.532 align:middle line:84%
>>SHULTS: But the
suggestion has also

00:13:56.532 --> 00:13:59.000 align:middle line:84%
been made that they could
be placed in areas of town

00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:01.880 align:middle line:84%
where there are a lot
of crime or rioting,

00:14:01.880 --> 00:14:04.970 align:middle line:84%
and that's a slippery
slope because then

00:14:04.970 --> 00:14:09.080 align:middle line:84%
just a few steps further,
and pretty soon machines

00:14:09.080 --> 00:14:11.180 align:middle line:84%
could be patrolling
the city's streets.

00:14:11.180 --> 00:14:12.530 align:middle line:90%
And so we don't want to--

00:14:12.530 --> 00:14:13.760 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Shooting at will.

00:14:13.760 --> 00:14:15.350 align:middle line:84%
>>SHULTS: And
that's the problem.

00:14:15.350 --> 00:14:17.670 align:middle line:84%
We don't want to see this
sort of thing happen.

00:14:17.670 --> 00:14:20.450 align:middle line:84%
The question is, how do we
circumvent this development

00:14:20.450 --> 00:14:24.120 align:middle line:84%
from becoming a standard
fixture in our lives?

00:14:24.120 --> 00:14:26.840 align:middle line:84%
The problem, in
my estimation, is

00:14:26.840 --> 00:14:31.950 align:middle line:84%
that we don't teach people
ethics along with technology.

00:14:31.950 --> 00:14:34.710 align:middle line:84%
And we need to focus on
ethics, what makes us human.

00:14:34.710 --> 00:14:38.207 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, and you can't
program ethics, can you?

00:14:38.207 --> 00:14:39.540 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: I would say you could.

00:14:39.540 --> 00:14:41.850 align:middle line:84%
I mean, consider that if you
can create a machine that

00:14:41.850 --> 00:14:46.170 align:middle line:84%
has a self-image and has an
understanding of rules and law,

00:14:46.170 --> 00:14:48.150 align:middle line:84%
perhaps you can take
it to the next step

00:14:48.150 --> 00:14:50.790 align:middle line:84%
and give it a sense of
morality and ethics.

00:14:50.790 --> 00:14:54.150 align:middle line:84%
Even if it doesn't
feel emotionally,

00:14:54.150 --> 00:14:58.140 align:middle line:84%
it could still
evaluate, at some level,

00:14:58.140 --> 00:15:02.380 align:middle line:84%
what would be the ethical
choice, minimal to no harm.

00:15:02.380 --> 00:15:04.360 align:middle line:90%
You see where I'm going.

00:15:04.360 --> 00:15:07.900 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Isn't this violating
all of Isaac Asimov's rules

00:15:07.900 --> 00:15:08.910 align:middle line:90%
of robots?

00:15:08.910 --> 00:15:09.710 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: Ah.

00:15:09.710 --> 00:15:12.190 align:middle line:84%
Well, see, this is
a very good point.

00:15:12.190 --> 00:15:17.530 align:middle line:84%
Asimov's fictional robotic
laws were really a benchmark

00:15:17.530 --> 00:15:20.410 align:middle line:84%
because for the very
first time, somebody

00:15:20.410 --> 00:15:23.380 align:middle line:84%
had quantified exactly
or codified perhaps

00:15:23.380 --> 00:15:26.620 align:middle line:84%
what it would take to
create robots that can work

00:15:26.620 --> 00:15:28.220 align:middle line:90%
within a human civilization.

00:15:28.220 --> 00:15:32.080 align:middle line:84%
The first law, you
can't harm a human

00:15:32.080 --> 00:15:35.680 align:middle line:84%
unless something horrible
happens that forces you to.

00:15:35.680 --> 00:15:38.230 align:middle line:84%
Second law, you can't
disobey humans' instructions

00:15:38.230 --> 00:15:40.900 align:middle line:84%
unless it violates the
first law, and so on.

00:15:40.900 --> 00:15:43.240 align:middle line:84%
But it was found that the
laws were inconsistent

00:15:43.240 --> 00:15:46.840 align:middle line:84%
because a machine could decide
that there's an overriding

00:15:46.840 --> 00:15:48.700 align:middle line:84%
law that you must do
everything you can

00:15:48.700 --> 00:15:50.170 align:middle line:90%
to prevent any harm to humans.

00:15:50.170 --> 00:15:52.180 align:middle line:84%
Well, that would end up
being a dictatorship.

00:15:52.180 --> 00:15:54.550 align:middle line:90%
So we would lose all choice.

00:15:54.550 --> 00:15:57.680 align:middle line:84%
So while in concept
it's a great idea,

00:15:57.680 --> 00:15:59.950 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't really
hold logically.

00:15:59.950 --> 00:16:02.350 align:middle line:84%
Nevertheless, you and
I have the ability

00:16:02.350 --> 00:16:04.300 align:middle line:84%
to figure out what's
right in a society.

00:16:04.300 --> 00:16:06.400 align:middle line:84%
You're free to do
anything you choose to do.

00:16:06.400 --> 00:16:07.520 align:middle line:90%
You have free will.

00:16:07.520 --> 00:16:09.760 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time,
you have an obligation

00:16:09.760 --> 00:16:12.490 align:middle line:90%
not to do any harm.

00:16:12.490 --> 00:16:14.160 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Fascinating.

00:16:14.160 --> 00:16:15.960 align:middle line:90%
But it could backfire.

00:16:15.960 --> 00:16:17.250 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: Well, it can.

00:16:17.250 --> 00:16:19.032 align:middle line:84%
Many times, people
will say, well,

00:16:19.032 --> 00:16:20.490 align:middle line:84%
we're doing this
for your own good.

00:16:20.490 --> 00:16:24.820 align:middle line:84%
And that typically is a false
face for the desire to control.

00:16:24.820 --> 00:16:27.880 align:middle line:84%
And I think that the
desire for one person

00:16:27.880 --> 00:16:31.140 align:middle line:84%
to control the lives of another
is probably a mental illness.

00:16:31.140 --> 00:16:32.070 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Absolutely.

00:16:32.070 --> 00:16:34.810 align:middle line:84%
So, Charles, what
is mind uploading?

00:16:34.810 --> 00:16:35.610 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: Ah.

00:16:35.610 --> 00:16:37.560 align:middle line:84%
This actually takes
off directly from what

00:16:37.560 --> 00:16:41.010 align:middle line:84%
we're seeing in the Neuralink,
the possibility of taking

00:16:41.010 --> 00:16:43.590 align:middle line:84%
the elements of your memory,
your personality, everything

00:16:43.590 --> 00:16:47.910 align:middle line:84%
that makes you you and uploading
a copy into the computer

00:16:47.910 --> 00:16:49.270 align:middle line:90%
and then activating it.

00:16:49.270 --> 00:16:50.998 align:middle line:84%
And so there's two
types of memories

00:16:50.998 --> 00:16:52.290 align:middle line:90%
that would have to be uploaded.

00:16:52.290 --> 00:16:55.140 align:middle line:84%
One is, of course, all
of your experiences,

00:16:55.140 --> 00:16:56.920 align:middle line:84%
and memories, and
things that you've done.

00:16:56.920 --> 00:16:59.550 align:middle line:84%
But the other one is the
procedures, the decisions

00:16:59.550 --> 00:17:02.670 align:middle line:84%
you make, and how you go about
it, your sense of ethics,

00:17:02.670 --> 00:17:04.800 align:middle line:84%
and morality, and
operational rules.

00:17:04.800 --> 00:17:07.500 align:middle line:84%
Once you get an image
like that in the computer

00:17:07.500 --> 00:17:09.869 align:middle line:84%
and you activate it,
there's a very good chance

00:17:09.869 --> 00:17:12.869 align:middle line:84%
that if the simulated world and
the computer that it inhabits

00:17:12.869 --> 00:17:17.069 align:middle line:84%
is realistic enough, it would
feel very much like it is you.

00:17:17.069 --> 00:17:21.119 align:middle line:84%
And so imagine going into
a studio, sitting down,

00:17:21.119 --> 00:17:23.790 align:middle line:84%
having some sort of scanning
procedure performed.

00:17:23.790 --> 00:17:26.220 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of that scan,
either one of two things

00:17:26.220 --> 00:17:27.819 align:middle line:90%
is going to happen.

00:17:27.819 --> 00:17:30.090 align:middle line:84%
You're going to
stand up and go home,

00:17:30.090 --> 00:17:33.630 align:middle line:84%
or you're going to realize
you're not where you were,

00:17:33.630 --> 00:17:35.945 align:middle line:84%
which would be a good
indication that you're the copy.

00:17:35.945 --> 00:17:38.070 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You may be the
copy-- the digital version.

00:17:38.070 --> 00:17:39.320 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: You may be the copy.

00:17:39.320 --> 00:17:41.790 align:middle line:84%
Now, there can be some
advantages to this.

00:17:41.790 --> 00:17:44.490 align:middle line:84%
If the body is killed,
the mind could live on.

00:17:44.490 --> 00:17:46.980 align:middle line:84%
And effectively, you
could be immortal.

00:17:46.980 --> 00:17:49.365 align:middle line:84%
One of the things to
consider is that you

00:17:49.365 --> 00:17:53.280 align:middle line:84%
don't know who might edit or
alter who and what you are.

00:17:53.280 --> 00:17:56.460 align:middle line:84%
And we tend to do
things like that.

00:17:56.460 --> 00:17:58.835 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They talk about us
living in a digital universe.

00:17:58.835 --> 00:17:59.960 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: Well, absolutely.

00:17:59.960 --> 00:18:02.198 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: If that's the
case, who's controlling it?

00:18:02.198 --> 00:18:03.490 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: And that's the thing.

00:18:03.490 --> 00:18:06.030 align:middle line:84%
So when we talk about
artificial intelligence,

00:18:06.030 --> 00:18:08.280 align:middle line:84%
we often think that people
will develop the elements

00:18:08.280 --> 00:18:09.540 align:middle line:90%
independently.

00:18:09.540 --> 00:18:12.150 align:middle line:84%
But as has usually
been the case,

00:18:12.150 --> 00:18:14.190 align:middle line:84%
we learn a lot from
nature and the world

00:18:14.190 --> 00:18:15.820 align:middle line:90%
and organisms around us.

00:18:15.820 --> 00:18:20.610 align:middle line:84%
And so it may well be that
uploaded mind sections will

00:18:20.610 --> 00:18:22.410 align:middle line:84%
be analyzed and
pressed into service

00:18:22.410 --> 00:18:26.520 align:middle line:84%
to become true AIs, sentient
machines in the near future.

00:18:26.520 --> 00:18:28.770 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Sandbox
scenario, what is that?

00:18:28.770 --> 00:18:31.140 align:middle line:84%
>>SHULTS: So a sandbox
is basically a safe place

00:18:31.140 --> 00:18:31.960 align:middle line:90%
to do something.

00:18:31.960 --> 00:18:34.200 align:middle line:84%
And when you create
a sandbox world,

00:18:34.200 --> 00:18:36.000 align:middle line:84%
think of it as
being a digital copy

00:18:36.000 --> 00:18:39.900 align:middle line:84%
or model of our world, something
that an artificial organism

00:18:39.900 --> 00:18:42.090 align:middle line:84%
or an uploaded
mind could inhabit.

00:18:42.090 --> 00:18:44.100 align:middle line:84%
And what you want to
do, if you create,

00:18:44.100 --> 00:18:46.470 align:middle line:84%
let's say, an AI
or a world of AIs,

00:18:46.470 --> 00:18:48.840 align:middle line:84%
you want to put them in an
isolated computer system that

00:18:48.840 --> 00:18:51.750 align:middle line:84%
isn't network to anything
else to provide a safety

00:18:51.750 --> 00:18:55.540 align:middle line:84%
barrier between the external
world and the sandbox world.

00:18:55.540 --> 00:18:58.480 align:middle line:84%
And so this would allow them
to live in this simulation.

00:18:58.480 --> 00:19:01.260 align:middle line:84%
You could present them
with problems or scenarios

00:19:01.260 --> 00:19:03.210 align:middle line:84%
and see them work
out the results

00:19:03.210 --> 00:19:05.110 align:middle line:90%
in a logical or useful manner.

00:19:05.110 --> 00:19:06.900 align:middle line:84%
And then you can
harvest that information

00:19:06.900 --> 00:19:08.620 align:middle line:90%
and apply it to the real world.

00:19:08.620 --> 00:19:10.500 align:middle line:84%
One of the things to
consider is a sandbox

00:19:10.500 --> 00:19:13.810 align:middle line:84%
can run 10, 100, 1,000
times faster than reality.

00:19:13.810 --> 00:19:17.040 align:middle line:84%
So for every second that
the sandbox is running,

00:19:17.040 --> 00:19:20.700 align:middle line:84%
the mind in the sandbox would
experience about 16 minutes

00:19:20.700 --> 00:19:22.200 align:middle line:90%
and 40 seconds.

00:19:22.200 --> 00:19:25.890 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are you scared about
artificial intelligence?

00:19:25.890 --> 00:19:28.980 align:middle line:10%
>>SHULTS: I have a very
cautionary feeling about it.

00:19:28.980 --> 00:19:31.470 align:middle line:10%
I mean, I've had a lot of
experience in the research

00:19:31.470 --> 00:19:32.670 align:middle line:10%
and the operation.

00:19:32.670 --> 00:19:36.270 align:middle line:84%
And I can see that there are
definite, definite possible

00:19:36.270 --> 00:19:37.500 align:middle line:90%
problems.

00:19:37.500 --> 00:19:41.460 align:middle line:84%
The sandbox scenario is one
way of isolating those problems

00:19:41.460 --> 00:19:42.900 align:middle line:90%
if you're very, very careful.

00:19:42.900 --> 00:19:45.090 align:middle line:84%
You can never allow
the sandbox world

00:19:45.090 --> 00:19:48.780 align:middle line:84%
to be interfaced to
the real world any more

00:19:48.780 --> 00:19:51.210 align:middle line:84%
than a face-to-face
conversation.

00:19:51.210 --> 00:19:53.370 align:middle line:84%
You don't want any
digital input or output

00:19:53.370 --> 00:19:56.310 align:middle line:84%
to the rest of the world
because there could be hazards.

00:19:56.310 --> 00:20:00.600 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you have hope for
the future with AI looming out

00:20:00.600 --> 00:20:01.500 align:middle line:90%
there?

00:20:01.500 --> 00:20:04.800 align:middle line:84%
>>SHULTS: Absolutely, I do
because there are many things

00:20:04.800 --> 00:20:06.960 align:middle line:84%
that an artificial
intelligence running

00:20:06.960 --> 00:20:09.600 align:middle line:84%
at a higher level of
intellectual capacity

00:20:09.600 --> 00:20:11.060 align:middle line:90%
than a human could solve.

00:20:11.060 --> 00:20:13.560 align:middle line:84%
There are a lot of issues that
we need solving in the world,

00:20:13.560 --> 00:20:14.910 align:middle line:90%
and that could be a benefit.

00:20:14.910 --> 00:20:17.820 align:middle line:84%
They can also run much
faster and devote more time

00:20:17.820 --> 00:20:22.170 align:middle line:84%
to that problem in a short
period compared to us.

00:20:22.170 --> 00:20:24.780 align:middle line:84%
So there's a lot of
benefit to be seen from AI.

00:20:24.780 --> 00:20:26.160 align:middle line:90%
It can do a lot of the drudgery.

00:20:26.160 --> 00:20:28.560 align:middle line:84%
It solved the protein
solving problem

00:20:28.560 --> 00:20:29.980 align:middle line:90%
and a number of other things.

00:20:29.980 --> 00:20:31.170 align:middle line:90%
But yeah, there are hazards.

00:20:31.170 --> 00:20:32.610 align:middle line:84%
We have to be
very, very cautious

00:20:32.610 --> 00:20:35.580 align:middle line:84%
because an AI on the
loose could literally

00:20:35.580 --> 00:20:38.670 align:middle line:84%
displace human thinking,
the human world.

00:20:38.670 --> 00:20:39.945 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: In every aspect.

00:20:39.945 --> 00:20:41.070 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: Pretty much, yes.

00:20:41.070 --> 00:20:43.590 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of it, it would
find it didn't need.

00:20:43.590 --> 00:20:45.867 align:middle line:84%
Living on electrical
power and computing space,

00:20:45.867 --> 00:20:47.700 align:middle line:84%
it wouldn't need any
of the resources we do.

00:20:47.700 --> 00:20:48.617 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's right.

00:20:48.617 --> 00:20:51.150 align:middle line:84%
Our dear friend William Henry,
again, on Gaia's "Deep Space"

00:20:51.150 --> 00:20:55.320 align:middle line:84%
talks about the possible
ramifications of AI.

00:20:55.320 --> 00:20:56.295 align:middle line:90%
>>SHULTS: Certainly.

