00:21:52.648 --> 00:21:54.690 align:middle line:84%
- Well, it's interesting
to talk about the phrase

00:21:54.690 --> 00:21:56.860 align:middle line:90%
"singularity" in this context.

00:21:56.860 --> 00:21:59.400 align:middle line:84%
So AI people call
this the singularity

00:21:59.400 --> 00:22:00.990 align:middle line:90%
for a very definite reason.

00:22:00.990 --> 00:22:03.540 align:middle line:84%
They liken it to the
physics of a black hole.

00:22:03.540 --> 00:22:05.400 align:middle line:84%
At the center of
a black hole, you

00:22:05.400 --> 00:22:07.650 align:middle line:84%
have the singularity,
essentially

00:22:07.650 --> 00:22:10.380 align:middle line:84%
a point of virtual
infinite density

00:22:10.380 --> 00:22:12.520 align:middle line:84%
and infinite
gravitational power.

00:22:12.520 --> 00:22:17.250 align:middle line:84%
And in that type
of crazy physics,

00:22:17.250 --> 00:22:20.620 align:middle line:84%
all of the physics that we
have don't seem to apply.

00:22:20.620 --> 00:22:24.300 align:middle line:10%
We don't know how to predict
things at the singularity.

00:22:24.300 --> 00:22:27.330 align:middle line:10%
And this is what AI
theorists are saying.

00:22:27.330 --> 00:22:30.570 align:middle line:10%
When computing intelligence
exceeds our own,

00:22:30.570 --> 00:22:32.640 align:middle line:10%
we, human beings, will
not have the ability

00:22:32.640 --> 00:22:36.270 align:middle line:10%
to predict the trajectory
of our civilization.

00:22:36.270 --> 00:22:38.940 align:middle line:10%
We're basically going to be
losing control over this car

00:22:38.940 --> 00:22:40.140 align:middle line:10%
that we think we're driving.

00:22:40.140 --> 00:22:43.500 align:middle line:84%
And it's now the dominant
intelligence will be beyond us.

00:22:43.500 --> 00:22:45.720 align:middle line:84%
And what will that
dominant intelligence do?

00:22:45.720 --> 00:22:48.570 align:middle line:84%
Will it merge with us as
Kurzweil thinks, a combination

00:22:48.570 --> 00:22:51.150 align:middle line:84%
of human machine,
hybrid intelligence,

00:22:51.150 --> 00:22:55.050 align:middle line:84%
where we'll be some
freakish bunch of creatures

00:22:55.050 --> 00:22:57.900 align:middle line:84%
living for 500 years
and IQs of 1,000,

00:22:57.900 --> 00:22:59.640 align:middle line:90%
totally unlike what we are?

00:22:59.640 --> 00:23:01.797 align:middle line:84%
Or will the computers
think, humanity,

00:23:01.797 --> 00:23:03.130 align:middle line:90%
let's pull a terminator on them?

00:23:03.130 --> 00:23:04.270 align:middle line:90%
We have no idea.

00:23:04.270 --> 00:23:05.070 align:middle line:90%
We don't know.

00:23:05.070 --> 00:23:08.790 align:middle line:84%
Or will they be our willing
slaves and make our world

00:23:08.790 --> 00:23:10.260 align:middle line:90%
a paradise?

00:23:10.260 --> 00:23:11.350 align:middle line:90%
Who knows?

00:23:11.350 --> 00:23:12.690 align:middle line:90%
That's why it's a singularity.

00:23:12.690 --> 00:23:13.800 align:middle line:84%
We can't really
predict any of this.

00:23:13.800 --> 00:23:14.250 align:middle line:90%
